    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-17T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-17T05:00:00-05:00" n="669"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13022: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-17T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 17, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 17—9:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>157. Legation’s 155, April 16, 10 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>].<note n="89"
                        xml:id="d669fn89">Not printed.</note> Following from Consul General at
                    Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 17, noon. Letter Chengtu April 13 states 29th Szechuan Army ran
                            away and Reds have obtained supplies, guns and ammunition hence their
                            present push. At that time did not believe evacuation Chengtu would be
                            necessary. Two messages from <hi rend="italic">Palos</hi> dated April
                            16th which Legation doubtless received state <hi rend="italic">inter
                                alia</hi> Chengtu British [and] American missionaries starting
                            preliminary evacuation <pb facs="0793" n="681" xml:id="pg_681"/> women
                            children toward Tzechow and Chungking. Ford plane going Chengtu 17th
                            assist evacuation.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
